    {
      "text": "Indexed\n68\n-7-80\n\ndeveloped his Logos idea to explain that Plato's eide exist in a mind, and that mind Philo called Logos rather than Nous; further, in 3-74 1 saw the macrometasomakosmos and it looked to be made up of abstract Forms --which I called phylogons-- indicating that what I saw existed in a mind, and that mind was Valis or was Valis' depending on whether Valis has a physical existence or not; so I did see what Philo was talking about; I did, then, see the Logos). Does this mean that ou",
